rComments: She did not teach a single lecture. She would post a pre-recorded video once a week (30-40 mins) instead of a normal 3 hours lecture. Very monotone and no enthusiasm. Final was difficult compared to midterm / assignments.

Didn't hold any live lectures. She posted pre-recorded lectures where she read the textbook almost word for word. No point in watching those. Had to teach myself everything by reading the textbook, which you must buy because it comes with online mandatory homework assignments. The TA did more teaching than the actual professor
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Test heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: There are no lectures for this online class. The professor creates 30-45 minutes maximum lecture videos each week for each chapter on BrightSpace. The lecture videos are directly from the textbook. The lectures are poor. If you want to pass this class, you need to depend on yourself to learn the material. Joining the DGDs helps out.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Test heavy']

rComments: I literally never write reviews but this prof is SO BAD that I had to! Extremely unclear instruction and made accounting much more confusing than it needed to be. Skipped over CRUCIAl basics of accounting. Exam are heavily weighted and don't reflect reviews. Would not recommend taking her section unless you absolutely have to.
Chourou is a great teacher! She gives lots of examples in class in order for the students to understand. Keep up to date with the homework or else good luck

Lamia is really good at teaching you how to walk, but on the exams and the practice, expect to run. I found her really mean and not helpful or caring, but she definitely had better days. The exam for this class is outrageously hard. I suggest finding a test bank and studying the hardest stuff you find on every chapter.

She is a very caring teacher, and she does her best I'm sure. However, it is very confusing how so many students did so poorly in her class. I understand accounting, in general, is a very hard class, but she put way too much weight on the final exam. Do well in the Wiley assignments, and good luck for the final cause that exam was out of line.
Just avoid her if u can, she is caring sure but that class is really hard and she doesn't do a good job as a prof to "Teach" the material to you very boring lectures and your exams are crazy hard.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Accessible outside class', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: The professor is nice person who enjoys what she does but her lectures are really ineffective and bland, the grade distribution is not good and her exams are very hard. You may practice and study a lot but you will get nowhere near what you expect. The choice is yours but I would say stay away if your care for your GPA.

I chose her cause I saw all the amazing reviews but tbh she did not live up to the hype. The lectures were useless. All she did was throw a question on the board and give you 10mins to solve it without teaching any of the material required to solve it. Her exam and midterm were insanely hard. This course is hard regardless, but she didn't help.

Professor Chourou is extremely engaging and effectively conveys the subject matter; however, like most accounting classes it difficult to catch up when fallen behind. It is important to do all practise problem right after the chapter has been thought to reinforce your understanding. Beware the final as it is extremely challenging but doable!!!
She is an excellent accounting prof. She is caring and very helpful.

Classes are really boring and dry, you could probably do just as good without attending. Just look over her slides and do ALL the practice problems. She'll give examples to do in class and spend 20 minutes waiting for everyone to do them which was really annoying. Wouldn't take her again. Also DO NOT FALL BEHIND!!

You do not need to go to class, the slides are good enough. The midterm is really easy but the final was super difficult. Make sure you do well on Wiley assignments so that it can improve your mark! For the final study cash flows inside and out

Great professor. Is very clear in her teaching and what she expects from her students. Wants everyone to succeed in her classes. No wonder the class average is always 5% higher than the other classes. Does exercises with you in class and is always available to answer questions. Take her class!
Professor Chourou is a sharp and caring  professor. I think Telfer needs more accounting professors like her.

Only two chances to show if you know the stuff:  final and a midterm. I skipped most of my classes and did okay just because the lectures are a regurgitation of the textbook. She's decent at presenting the textbook content exactly as written - but useless at creating meaningful examples or clarifications when students ask.

Great prof! very sharp and organized...and really cares about her students!

Very sharp and serious Prof. Always there to help students. She knows the subject, which is not surprising having two PhDs!!! I strongly recommend her for serious students who really want to learn accounting.

This is the second time I took ADM 1340. I used to hate accounting until I had Prof. Chourou. She is an excellent Prof that really cares about her students. I like her style, way of conducting the lecture and explaining difficult materials. Take her if you can and avoid those part-time professors who are there only for the money.
Not recommended. She knows her stuff, just not a good communicator. Avoid if possible.
